# ğŸ§± AZ-900 â€“ Platform as a Service (PaaS)

## âœ… What is PaaS?

> Platform as a Service (PaaS) gives you a **preconfigured platform** to build and deploy apps â€” no hardware or OS to manage.

You focus on:
- Writing code
- Managing your app
- Storing your data

The provider handles:
- Infra
- OS
- Middleware
- DB engines
- Dev tools

---

## ğŸ”„ Shared Responsibility (PaaS)

| Layer                          | Managed By         |
|--------------------------------|--------------------|
| Physical infra, OS, DB engine  | âœ… Cloud provider   |
| Application code & data        | âœ… You              |
| Access, identity, some networking | ğŸ” Shared (varies)  |

---

## ğŸ’¡ Benefits of PaaS

- No hardware/OS management
- Prebuilt tools & frameworks
- Easy scaling + high availability built-in
- Lower maintenance overhead

---

## ğŸ“¦ Common PaaS Use Cases

| Scenario               | Description |
|------------------------|-------------|
| **Development framework** | Build apps with built-in SDKs, services, auto scaling |
| **Analytics / BI**        | Mine data, analyze trends, forecast (e.g. Synapse, Power BI) |

---

## ğŸ§  Summary

| Category         | PaaS |
|------------------|------|
| Control level     | Mid â€“ you manage apps + data |
| Responsibility    | Split (app = you, platform = provider) |
| Ideal for         | Developers, agile teams, analytics platforms |

---

# ğŸ“¦ AZ-900 â€“ Software as a Service (SaaS)

## âœ… What is SaaS?

> **Software as a Service (SaaS)** delivers **fully managed applications** over the internet.  
> You just sign in and use the app â€” no setup, patching, or infrastructure management.

---

## ğŸ’» Common SaaS Examples

- Outlook / Gmail (email)
- Microsoft Teams / Slack (messaging)
- QuickBooks / FreshBooks (finance)
- Microsoft 365 / Google Workspace (productivity)

---

## ğŸ”„ Shared Responsibility (SaaS)

| Layer                          | Managed By         |
|--------------------------------|--------------------|
| App development, patching      | âœ… Provider         |
| Physical infra, OS, middleware | âœ… Provider         |
| Data you enter                 | âœ… You              |
| Device and access security     | âœ… You              |

---

## âš¡ SaaS Characteristics

| Feature            | Description |
|--------------------|-------------|
| **Least flexible** | You canâ€™t change backend configs |
| **Most ready-to-use** | Instant deployment, no infra to manage |
| **Lowest technical burden** | Users need no coding or setup experience |
| **Scales easily** | Add/remove users or features on demand |

---

## ğŸ§  Summary

| Category         | SaaS |
|------------------|------|
| Control level     | ğŸ”½ Low â€“ provider manages almost everything |
| Responsibility    | You handle data, identity, and device control |
| Ideal for         | Businesses needing ready-to-use apps with no infra headaches |

